- The average temperature is calculated across all data entries in the `environmental_data` table;
- The data entries are considered only if they fall within the specified time range of January 1, 2022, to December 31, 2022.

- 'Heavy mist' refers to average humidity greater than 60%;
- 'Warm summer day' refers to average temperature greater than 25 degrees Celsius;
- 'Monitoring the environment in more than one organ' refers to sensor types present in more than one floor level.

- 'CO2 concentration in ppm' refers to the parts per million of carbon dioxide in the air;
- 'Occupancy status (1 for occupied, 0 for unoccupied)' indicates whether a room is in use;
- 'Data quality' refers to the reliability of the environmental data collected;
- '700 ppm' is a threshold for CO2 concentration that is considered above normal indoor levels.

